President
Muhammadu Buhari,  has, on behalf of the
Federal Executive Council, congratulated the Sultan of Sokoto, His Eminence,
Muhammad Sa’ad Abubakar III on the occasion of his 63rd birthday anniversary. A statement by Mallam Garba Shehu, Senior Special Assistant to the President (Media & Publicity), Saturday said as head of Jama’atu Nasirl Islam (JNI), President-General of the Nigerian Supreme Council for Islamic Affairs (NSCIA) and co-Chairman of Nigeria Inter-Religious Council (NIREC), President Buhari applauds the Sultan’s exemplary roles and contributions towards building a peaceful, secure and prosperous country. He
said the President values the timely counsel and support of the royal father to
this administration’s policies and programmes, commending His Eminence for
championing poverty reduction, healthcare and education for the most
vulnerable, during his reign as a spiritual and traditional leader of the
people. “President
Buhari joins family members, the Sokoto Emirate, the government and people of
Sokoto State, friends and well-wishers in praying that Almighty Allah grants
the Sultan more years of health and happiness to keep doing the things he loves
most: building bridges of peace, tolerance and development across Nigeria,”the
statement said.